      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait really? i thought the whole point of originalism was to stick to the text as they wrote it. wouldn't the court be overreaching if they ignored the literal wording of the amendment just to fit modern safety concerns? isn't the \"militia\" part just a historical context thing rather than a limitation?",
