      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. you keep saying it's \"judicial activism\" and \"dangerous,\" but isn't that just how people who disagree with the court describe it? wouldn't an originalist argument say that \"shall not be infringed\" is pretty clear-cut and that the court is actually doing its job by following the literal text? why do you think the \"militia\" part is a more valid way to read it than just looking at the individual right mentioned right after?",
